### Lab Test Management API - REST Client
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/v1
@contentType = application/json

### 1. GET All Tests
GET {{baseUrl}}/tests
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 2. CREATE New Test (Online - with Schema)
POST {{baseUrl}}/test/add
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Complete Blood Count pro",
  "testId": "693d9f18a2469caf76ab7826",
  "categoryId": "693d9f18a2469caf76ab7825",
  "schemaId": "69498dad079c05581bbcbd4b",
  "price": 500
}

### 3. CREATE Test without Schema (Offline)
POST {{baseUrl}}/test/add
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Blood Sugar Random",
  "testId": "693d9f18a2469caf76ab7827",
  "categoryId": "693d9f18a2469caf76ab7825",
  "schemaId": null,
  "price": 150
}

### 4. GET Single Test by testId
GET {{baseUrl}}/test/693d9f18a2469caf76ab7826
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 5. UPDATE Test Price
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/test/693d9f18a2469caf76ab7826/update-price
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "price": 600
}

### 6. UPDATE Test Schema
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/test/693d9f18a2469caf76ab7826/update-schema
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "schemaId": "69498dad079c05581bbcbd4b"
}

### 7. UPDATE Test Schema to NULL (Remove Schema - Makes Test Offline)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/test/693d9f18a2469caf76ab7826/update-schema
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "schemaId": null
}

### 8. DELETE Test (Hard Delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/test/693d9f18a2469caf76ab7826
